
[1]glaucoma

   GLAUCO'MA, n. [Gr.] A fault in the eye, in which the crystalline humor
   becomes gray, but without injury to the sight.

   A disease in the eye, in which the crystalline humor becomes of a
   bluish or greenish color,and its transparency is diminished.

   An opacity of the vitreous humor.

      According to Sharp, the glaucoma of the Greeks is the same as the
    cataract; and according to St. Yves and others, it is a cataract with
                                 amaurosis.
